# Vercel Environment Variables - Ready to Import (for Token Exchange / Swap)
# ========================================================================
#
# CRITICAL: Token Exchange (the swap feature) will NOT work until this key is set
# correctly and a new production build has run with it.
#
# RECOMMENDED NAME: NEXT_PUBLIC_KIT_KEY   <--- Use this one
#
# STEPS:
# 1. Copy everything below this line.
# 2. Replace the placeholder value with your real Circle App Kit key
#    (format is usually: KIT_KEY:xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx:yyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyy)
# 3. Open: https://vercel.com/siribraheems-projects/arcpay-web-app
# 4. Go to Settings → Environment Variables
# 5. Click the "Import" button and paste the content
# 6. Make sure the boxes for Production, Preview, AND Development are all selected
# 7. Save / Import
# 8. After import, find your latest Production deployment and click "Redeploy"
#    (or push any small change to the GitHub repo — it will auto-deploy)
#
# The swap panel will then enable and the yellow warning banner will disappear.
#
# NEVER commit a file with your real key to GitHub.

NEXT_PUBLIC_KIT_KEY=your_real_circle_app_kit_key_here_KIT_KEY_xxx_yyy

# You can also set it under these fallback names if you prefer (the code supports them now):
# KIT_KEY=your_real_circle_app_kit_key_here
# CIRCLE_KIT_KEY=your_real_circle_app_kit_key_here

# Optional for Privy auth (if used):
# NEXT_PUBLIC_PRIVY_APP_ID=your_privy_app_id_here
